{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567253","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567253"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:58:05+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:58:05+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18953"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18953","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18953"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.81,0.03,0.03,0.05,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11687"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80493"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11687","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11687"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18953"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65780"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"88"},{"type":"tags","id":"483"},{"type":"tags","id":"3505"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11304"},{"type":"tags","id":"11309"},{"type":"tags","id":"11310"},{"type":"tags","id":"11396"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"},{"type":"tags","id":"12912"},{"type":"tags","id":"12921"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27498"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27499"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80493","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80493"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 72-year-old woman dies in hospital from complications of pneumonia. She had a history of chronic obstructive pulmonary disease and type 2 diabetes mellitus. The treating doctor needs to complete the death certificate.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct documentation of cause of death on the death certificate?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document direct cause followed by antecedent causes and other significant conditions in sequence","List all medical conditions in chronological order of diagnosis","Record only the final event that led to death","Include all active medical problems at time of death","State a single primary cause of death"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach is to \u003Cstrong\u003Edocument direct cause followed by antecedent causes and other significant conditions in sequence\u003C/strong\u003E. Death certificates require a logical chain of events leading to death, starting with the direct cause and working backwards through the sequence of conditions that led to death. Each condition should include the approximate time interval between its onset and death.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EList all medical conditions in chronological order of diagnosis\u003C/strong\u003E - This does not show the causal relationship between conditions leading to death\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecord only the final event that led to death\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the important underlying conditions that contributed to the death\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInclude all active medical problems at time of death\u003C/strong\u003E - Only conditions directly contributing to death should be included in the causal sequence\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EState a single primary cause of death\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to show the sequence of events and multiple contributing factors\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn this case, an appropriate sequence might be: 1a) Respiratory failure (2 days), 1b) Pneumonia (5 days), 1c) Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease (8 years). Type 2 diabetes would be listed in Part 2 as a contributing condition.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Death certificates must include the sequence of medical conditions leading to death, with the immediate cause listed first.","The time interval between onset of each condition and death should be documented on the death certificate.","Conditions contributing to but not directly causing death are listed separately on the death certificate."],"references":["Australian Bureau of Statistics. Cause of death certification guide. [online]. 2024. [Cited on 20 Jan 2025]. Available at: https://www.abs.gov.au/statistics/detailed-methodology-information/cause-death-certification-guide/latest-release","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65780"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18953"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65780","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65780"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T21:25:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T22:58:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11687"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80493"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relati